div.p:
               I owe you, dear Mr Deane, an acknowledgement of your kind letter and sending of Melaleuca-twig since some days;

Letter not found. See also M to W. Woolls, 13 September 1886.
                — but it is only at quiet Sunday-hour now, that I can attend to your plant. It seems to me a species of its own, and so I named it after you;



                     M described 
                        Melaleuca deanei in B87.13.06, p. 1106.
                but — as remarked in the description, which is soon to pass into print, it may perhaps be a luxuriant form of M. parviflora; in that case the specific name will stand as that of variety.
